By Jaguar Mephistopheles
I really enjoy the mix of the classic and the newer songs, including some of the updated versions, such as "Heat Miser" and "Let It Snow". The whole album is very upbeat and fun without being vapid. It's quite a secular mix, without any really religious songs. And the star parade is unbelievably high caliber and eclectic: Chris Isaak, Mary J Blige, The Ramones, Brian Setzer Orchestra, Dolly Parton, etc. I am thinking I will be tracking down the other Body Works Christmas mixes.
